    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR3l0099-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-h" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-14T03:27:30.036+09:00">Preface</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T02:58:12.295+09:00">and I may have gathered left-out material from those times</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T03:37:50.827+09:00">and what presumably was heard or seen not just by one person's ears and one person's</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T02:59:21.084+09:00">but how would I then go on to presume to imagine that nothing there was without base.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T02:57:55.697+09:00">I may have investigated early records in the surviving documents,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:10:02.708+09:00">Wei Suo lost his state</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:10:55.326+09:00">and (regarding this fact) there are two conflicting oral reports.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:22:58.836+09:00">On Lü Wang's service to the Zhou</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:23:20.679+09:00">Zizhang preserves two explanations.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:43:00.769+09:00">Comparable examples of this kind</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:43:22.679+09:00">are often found in the records.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:44:39.387+09:00">From this point of view</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:45:03.019+09:00">the difficulty of oral and written evidence</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:45:38.452+09:00">has a very long history.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:19:24.429+09:00">The fixed formulations of the documents and reports</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:19:53.305+09:00">base themselves on the formal volumes of state histories</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:21:22.5+09:00">and the situation remains the same.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:06:15.761+09:00">How much more will this be the case when one looks up and transmits what comes from a thousand years ago</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:06:51.694+09:00">and when one records systematic accounts of different customs</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:07:24.189+09:00">and sticks together disjointed words on damaged and deficient documents,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:08:23.008+09:00">when one seeks information on actions from old times</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:23:33.455+09:00">and insists on having things not look ambiguous</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:09:47.713+09:00">and one's account not to be contradictory</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:10:33.751+09:00">before they can be regarded reliable,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:24:31.427+09:00">then this is where former historical accounts present problems.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:26:11.381+09:00">But if the states have not for that reason discontinued the offices of commentators and archivists</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:15:54.042+09:00">and if the scholars do not discontinue their business of reciting and reading their sources</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:17:20.423+09:00">surely this is because what they miss out on is of little importance, by comparison,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:17:05.666+09:00">and what they preserve this way is much more important.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:17:54.492+09:00">What I have collected at this point</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:18:22.952+09:00">setting out to continue what has been transmitted</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:18:39.744+09:00">cannot be deemed my fault.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:27:54.374+09:00">If in my modern enquiries in our present world</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:28:11.194+09:00">there are mistakes and confusions</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:28:52.894+09:00">it is my quiet hope to share with earlier worthies and earlier scholars</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:30:14.761+09:00">the criticism and maligning I will be exposed to.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:22:03.205+09:00">As I write up and transmit these things</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:22:55.929+09:00">it will serve to throw light on what is not completely wrong in the way of the spirits.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
